Package Battleship

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Ship
    This Interface is to be implemented by all different types of ship where they have to define how each method works for its own specifications.
    User
    This interface is inherited all the players that are playing.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BoardLocation
    This objects help convert pixel values of the GUI to the Board's X and Y Coordinates.
    Colors
    This object is a way to coordinate all the colors present on the GUI.
    Computer
    This class takes cake of all actions performed by the Computer's point of view.
    GameHelper
    This class helps run the Game Logic.
    GameOverWindow
    Creates the GameOverWindow which pops up when the the player either wins or loses.
    Gamers
    The Main Class where the PlayerWindow and GameOverWindow are declared.
    Location
    This object represents the specification of each button the GUI Window
    Player
    This class keeps track of all the operations necessary for the player.
    PlayerWindow
    Creates the Battleship Window on which the player plays the game.
